\subsubsection{Eigenvalues of the drift matrix}

Figure~\ref{fig:drift_eigenvalues} shows the eigenvalues of the drift matrix $M$ for both variants.
In the baseline model, the eigenvalues of the unconstrained $M$ depend entirely on the learned parameters and may have positive real parts, corresponding to an explosive (non-mean-reverting) drift direction.
In the stable variant, $M = -(V^\top V + \epsilon I)$ is negative definite by construction, so all eigenvalues are bounded above by $-\epsilon$.

